<br>
I'm sitting here thinking... You know, maybe people just think that all young kids deserve a beating when they try or attempt to rival an adult in debate or ranting, such as the soapbox..<br>
<br>
I also sense I'm getting some pity too, maybe it feels nice to have people sticking up for you. Though, I just get that feeling that I have alot of pity spared on me cause of my age.<br>
<br>
Sure, I condemn parents beating there children, for discipline reasons only. Hell, I used to get the belt when I was little, and if I get into trouble, ill get shoved around a bit. <br>
<br>
All in all I know someone in my school, whom parents are afraid of there son... What the Fu.... ? <br>
<br>
You guys do know that, I was suggested by a friend, reason why I'm LFG for a long time is, people read the soapbox and say, &quot;Gee that moron is sure smart, I wont group with him, cause if he can't post, then he can't play his chara.&quot; <br>
<br>
Not to say that I already know that this will happen... Yeah sure I don't mind the little abuse, maybe get slammed everyday, but Jesus Christ on a Crutch! <br>
<br>
I don't want a whole &quot;faction&quot; war started over me cause I'm just &quot;14&quot; and I post to entertain and annoy people, and make the soapbox a little interesting...<br>
<br>
Sure my intentions where good, but hey! Look now! When I actually do rant, it gets treated like trash! Again, I do realize the price posting stupid stuff has against your reputation...<br>
<br>
From now on, I won't do anything other than rant in the soapbox... For those the remotely found my posts amusing, or the funny gentle slams that came after it... Well get over the loss, its not happening anymore. <br>
<br>
I have to save my reputation at one point, and Naktah's comment drew the line for me. I intend not to cross it.<br>
<br>
No more misspelling for me, I'm in a very high standard English class, and I have to get my stuff together... <br>
<br>
Reason why I'm not pissed at Omi? It's because he can be an over-wrought Zealous bastard. Though i have known that, and I do respect him. <br>
<br>
He dose give out good advice. I do belive though he lets the heat of the moment get to him alot though. <br>
<br>
Well good night guys, Doing a project on Cronos, Father of Time for my Mythology class, gotta get working on it. <br>
