2. Learn some grammar.<br>
3. Learn how to arrange your thoughts in a sequence others can understand.<br>
4. Learn how to convert those thoughts into nice grammatical constructions.<br>
<br>
1 &amp; 2 are pointless without 3 &amp; 4.  And, if you can only find time to become skilled at one of those four, pick #3.  Hiring someone to fixup your grammar and edit your run-ons into paragraphs is a helluva lot cheaper than hiring someone to iron your wrinkled thoughts and starch your allegories. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/bfirionavie.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaehunleifong>Jaehun Leifong</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.everquest.co.kr/live_class_img/live_class_monk.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#3300FF>Got Jae?<br>
